(49, 'one-north Park: Mediapolis', 'one-north Park is a 16-ha park consisting of 13 land parcels spanning across the entire length of one-north and is a key element in JTC\'s masterplan for one-north to create a work-live-play-learn environment. When fully completed, it will serve as an integrated green link connecting key developments such as Biopolis, Fusionopolis, Mediapolis and the one-north MRT station.\r\n\r\none-north Park: Mediapolis is a 1.98 ha park located in the heart of Mediapolis, fronting the MediaCorp campus. The park consists of a street level park and also a rooftop park above a Multi-Utility Hub that consists of a car park and other infrastructure facilities.\r\n\r\nThe street level park boasts many butterfly-attracting shrubs such as Lantana camara and Caesalpinia pulcherrima, and the Multi-Utility Hub is covered with Thunbergia grandiflora creepers growing on the trellis. The rooftop park boasts a meadow-themed landscape, and two large event lawns (oval and square lawn) that can be used for recreation and community events.\r\n\r\nLocation: Media Circle, next to MediaCorp campus\r\n\r\nPark Size: 1.98 hectares\r\n\r\nLighting hours: 7.00pm to 7.00am\r\n\r\nNearby Parks/Park Connectors: one-north Park: Fusionopolis South\r\n\r\nAccessibility: Wheelchair accessible\r\n', 103.792829540115, 1.29493834487393, 1),
