(171, 'Yishun Neighbourhood Park', 'Developed on an old rubber estate, Yishun Neighbourhood Park is the place to go to if you are looking for a quiet retreat. Featuring a hill with an open lawn at the top and facilities such as a children\'s playground and fitness equipment, the park is a great place for families looking for a day of fun.\r\n\r\nFitness enthusiasts can warm up at the exercise stations before taking a jog around the park. The open lawn at the top of the hill is also ideal for picnics with friends and family.\r\n\r\nLocation: Bound by Yishun Ave 2, Ave 7 and St 22. Yishun St 20 leads straight to the park\r\n\r\nPark size: 7.7 hectares\r\n\r\nPark lighting hours: 7pm-7am\r\n\r\nAccessibility info: Wheelchair accessible', 103.835077000931, 1.43762199315966, 1),
